{
  "text": "Data from study reports were extracted onto electronic coding forms that could hold up to 205 items from each study. All studies were coded by the first two authors, independent of each other. They then met and reviewed each item for agreement. If agreement could not be reached, the last two authors served as adjudicators. Using Cohen's kappa statistic (k), [CITATION_1] the overall agreement rate prior to making corrections was 0.96 for the studies included in the current analysis.",
  "citation_candidates": [
